The Game class represents a card game, managing players, the deck of cards, and player money.

Hand
The Hand class represents a player's hand in a blackjack game, managing the cards, betting, and game rules related to the hand.

The HumanPlayer class represents a human player in the blackjack game.

The InputValidator class is responsible for validating user input.
LargeDeck
The LargeDeck class represents a deck of playing cards consisting of multiple standard decks combined into one.

The OutcomeCalculator class is responsible for calculating the outcome of a player's hand in relation to the dealer's hand in a card game.
Player
The Player interface represents a generic player in the blackjack game.
Rank
Enum representing the ranks of playing cards, from Two to Ace.
Round
The Round class manages a single round of play in a card game.
SmallDeck
The SmallDeck class represents a specialized version of a deck of cards.
Step
The Step record represents a single action.
StepType
Enum representing the types of steps that can occur during a card game.
Suit
Enum representing the suits of playing cards.
ValueCalculator
The ValueCalculator class provides utility methods for calculating the total value of a collection of cards in a card game.
